<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-07T09:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-07T09:44:00-05:00" n="453" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.7962/77: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-07T14:00:00-00:44">April 7,
                                    1942—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>120. Roberts Field lease agreement and contract for Grumman service
                            concluded and signed today by Liberian Government and Panair. Lease for
                            Fisherman Lake will probably be signed April 9.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wharton</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>